{{Infobox artwork | title = Drosophila Fly Head | image = Drosophila Fly Head (1988) by Wayne Chabre, Eugene, Oregon.jpg | image_size = | caption = The sculpture in October 2015 | artist = [[Wayne Chabre]] | catalogue = | year = {{start date|1988}} | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | type = Sculpture | material = Copper | subject = Fly | height_imperial = 3.5 | width_imperial = 3 | length_imperial = 2.5 | metric_unit = m <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = ft <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = Undetermined (1993) | city = [[Eugene, Oregon]], United States | coordinates = {{coord|44.04640|-123.07217|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = University of Oregon Campus | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = Location on the University of Oregon campus | owner = [[University of Oregon]] }} '''''Drosophila Fly Head''''' is an outdoor 1988 sculpture by [[Wayne Chabre]], installed on the [[University of Oregon]] campus in [[Eugene, Oregon]], in the United States. The hammered copper sheet high-relief of a fly head measures approximately {{Convert|3.5|ft|m}} x {{Convert|3|ft|m}} x {{Convert|2.5|ft|m}}. It was surveyed by the [[Smithsonian Institution]]'s "[[Save Outdoor Sculpture!]]" program in March 1993, though its condition was undetermined. The sculpture is administered by the University of Oregon.<ref name=SI>{{cite web|title=Drosophila Fly Head, (sculpture).|url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!328548~!0#focus|publisher=[[Smithsonian Institution]]|accessdate=January 24, 2016}}</ref>
